cs.LG, cs.CL, cs.IR, cs.AI, cs.CV

The paper discusses the use of neural networks for large-scale multi-label text classification tasks, which falls under the categories of machine learning (cs.LG), natural language processing (cs.CL), information retrieval (cs.IR), artificial intelligence (cs.AI), and computer vision (cs.CV). However, since the focus is on neural network architectures and training techniques, cs.LG is the most likely category, followed by cs.CL and cs.IR.
